text: Prior to the Synod of Ráth Breasail the Catholic Church in Ireland did not have a diocesan system of governance. The reforming councils of the Church brought Ireland into line with the rest of the Church and established a diocesan system. Today twenty-six dioceses remain while others have been merged and still others have become extinct or used as titular sees. ==Titular dioceses== *Inis Cathaigh *Ceanannus Mór *Glendalough *Slebte *Cluain Iraird ==References== * Irish titular sees
